<h1 class="title">Reference</h1>
<span class="subtitle"></span>
<!-- $$$mkspecs-reference.html-description -->
<div class="descr"> <a name="details"></a>
<p>The reference sections describes in detail additonnal variables and functions that are available for use in qmake project files.</p>
<a name="variable-reference"></a>
<h2 id="variable-reference">Variable Reference</h2>
<p><a href="mkspecs-variable-reference.html">Variables</a> describes the additonnal variables that are recognized by qmake when configuring the build process for projects.</p>
<p><a href="mkspecs-pseudo-variable-reference.html">Pseudo Variables</a> describes the variables that are evaluated late in project build process. In contrary to standard variables, they only use a single dollar-sign and their contents is not available during project file processing.</p>
<p><b>Note: </b>Pseudo variables requires <b>qmake 3.0 (Qt 5.0)</b> or later, except if used in:</p><ul>
<li>output variables: <code>DESTDIR</code>, <code>DLLDESTDIR</code>, <a href="mkspecs-variable-reference.html#installdir">INSTALLDIR</a>.</li>
<li>include variables: <a href="mkspecs-variable-reference.html#iquotepath">IQUOTEPATH</a>, <code>INCLUDEPATH</code>.</li>
<li>dependencies variables: <code>LIBS</code>, <a href="mkspecs-variable-reference.html#plugins">PLUGINS</a>, <code>PRE_TARGETDEPS</code>, <code>POST_TARGETDEPS</code>.</li>
<li>installation variables (i.e&#x2e; <code>INSTALLS</code> sub-variables).</li>
</ul>
<a name="function-reference"></a>
<h2 id="function-reference">Function Reference</h2>
<p>These functions are divided into categories according to their type:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="mkspecs-replace-function-reference.html">Replace Functions</a></li>
<li><a href="mkspecs-test-function-reference.html">Test Functions</a></li>
</ul>
